HEADWORD: clutches
<hw>clutches</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>the act of
grasping.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> clasp, clench, clutch, grasp, grip, hold.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>control; power; -- used in the phrase <ecol><b>in
one's clutches</b></ecol>. Same as <er>clutch{2}</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>clutch hitter</ent>⟦br⟧
